        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 20 miles north of Harlowton to 17 miles
north of Big Timber, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, along with brief heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Harlowton, Deadmans Basin Reservoir, Judith Gap, Shawmut and
Melville.

Expect gusty cross winds along US-191.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
